	<xs:complexType name="DuctileShearStructureType">
		<xs:annotation>
			<xs:documentation>Package : GeologicStructure ; Date 2007-05-12 15:32:34 
 a parallel-sided zone of localised shearing displacement; may contain sigmoidal mineral-filled veins, locally well-developed cleavage or foliation, wholesale grain size reduction or mylonitisation, or a combination of these features
a discrete tabular zone (very thin compared to its along-strike and down dip dimensions) of plastic deformation across which there has been shear displacement. DuctileShearStructure is a map-scale feature. 
</xs:documentation>
		</xs:annotation>
		<xs:complexContent>
			<xs:extension base="gsml:ShearDisplacementStructureType">
				<xs:sequence>
					<xs:element name="segment" type="gsml:DuctileShearStructurePropertyType" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="unbounded"/>
				</xs:sequence>
			</xs:extension>
		</xs:complexContent>
	</xs:complexType>
